        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.14579/2606.14579v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Motivation of VISTA.In vanilla GRPO, multiple rollouts from the same screenshot can produce homogeneous rewards, yielding zero relative advantage.\nVISTA constructs the group from target-preserving views of the same GUI instance.\nThese views preserve the instruction and target semantics while changing the screenshot geometry.\nAs a result, VISTA turns homogeneous fixed-view rewards into informative cross-view variation.",
                "position": 323
            }
        ]
